### 📄 Project-Upgrade Overview (share with the team)

| Step | Branch | Goal | Tool Prompt |
|------|--------|------|-------------|
| **0  (helpers pass)** | **`pg-upgrade-branch`** (latest) | Scan *current* SQLite-only SQL and replace hard-wired fragments (`?`, `strftime`, plain JSON text, …) with **lightweight helper calls** that already live in `src/storage/sqlHelpers.ts`. No Postgres logic exists yet—this is the first conversion pass. | **Prompt 0** (below) |
| **1  (report)** | **`fix/pg-collector`** (legacy) | Mine every spot where the old code added Postgres-specific casting or time manipulation (`::TEXT`, `extract(epoch …)` …). Produce a machine-readable JSON **casting report** keyed by file/function/fragment. | Prompt 1 |
| **2  (apply)** | **`pg-upgrade-branch`** (work tree after step 0) | Read the casting report and apply helper-based equivalents so the new branch gains 100 % of the legacy behaviour **without** re-introducing `config.postgresEnabled` branches. Add any missing helpers. | Prompt 2 |
| **3  (audit)** | **`pg-upgrade-branch`** (final) | Compare the final codebase against the casting report. Flag residual PG-only fragments or missing helper calls. Emit a markdown audit table. | Prompt 3 |

Outcome: the modern branch keeps its clean, single-path SQL while inheriting every subtle Postgres adjustment the legacy branch had.

